\section{FWER scope}{

Cluster-level \emph{p}-values within each pair are already
max-statistic FWER-controlled by \code{\link[=rel_cluster_test]{rel_cluster_test()}}. The
Holm/Bonferroni adjustment in \code{run_between_pairwise()} controls
family-wise error across the K-choose-2 \emph{pair comparisons} (a
second layer above the cluster test's internal control), not
over individual pixels or clusters.

For each pair, the statistic carried into the across-pairs
adjustment is the \strong{minimum cluster-level \emph{p}-value within that
pair} (i.e., the most-significant cluster's \emph{p}). Within-pair
cluster \emph{p}-values are not re-adjusted: they remain the
max-statistic FWER-controlled values from \code{rel_cluster_test()}.
A pair with no clusters at all contributes \code{p_min = 1.0} so the
Holm ordering is well-defined.
}

